(x, y, z) &= (\rho \sin \theta \cos \phi, \rho \sin \theta \sin \phi, \rho \cos \theta),
\end{align*}where $\rho > 0,$ $0 \le \theta \le \pi,$ and $0 \le \phi \le 2 \pi.$
From this we discover that $\phi = \boxed{\frac{2 \pi}{9}}$ and $\rho = \boxed{2}.$
